org.apache.flink.types

接口 Key<T>

  • 所有超级接口:
    Comparable<T>, IOReadableWritable, Serializable, Value
    所有已知子接口:
    NormalizableKey<T>
    所有已知实现类:
    BooleanValue, ByteValue, CharValue, DoubleValue, FloatValue, IntValue, LongValue, NullValue, ShortValue, StringValue
    已过时。 
    The Key type is a relict of a deprecated and removed API and will be removed in future (2.0) versions as well.

    @Deprecated
 @PublicEvolving
public interface Key<T>
extends Value, Comparable<T>
    This interface has to be implemented by all data types that act as key. Keys are used to establish relationships between values. A key must always be Comparable to other keys of the same type. In addition, keys must implement a correct Object.hashCode() method and Object.equals(Object) method to ensure that grouping on keys works properly.

    This interface extends Value and requires to implement the serialization of its value.

    另请参阅:
    Value, IOReadableWritable, Comparable
